            <title>[DERBY-1562] Have BaseJDBCTestCase have a Connection field to cover the common case where one connection is used.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1562</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Most JDBC tests that extend BaseJDBCTestCase  have their own connection field and their own tearDown method to close the connection, this is all common code that should be in the base class. Once the getConnection method becomes an instance method (rather than a static method see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1555&quot; title=&quot;API for configuration information in Derby&amp;#39;s JUnit tests should through instance methods of the base classes, not static methods and static fields&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-1555&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-1555&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) then it could create the connection on demand.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
